                    },
                    "body": "Reformat issue and summary.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-13T15:10:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-13T15:10:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13582",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fadoe",
                        "name": "fadoe",
                        "displayName": "Falk Doering",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thank you for the changes in svn revison 4150. But please remove \"'\", it will be stored in the database, too.\nWrong:\n{code}\nreturn \"'\" . $this->_connection->real_escape_string($value) . \"'\";\n{code}\n-> output var_dump: string(19) \"'this is my string'\"\n\nRight:\n{code}\nreturn $this->_connection->real_escape_string($value);\n{code}\n-> output var_dump: string(17) \"this is my string\"",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fadoe",
                        "name": "fadoe",
                        "displayName": "Falk Doering",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-21T08:57:06.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-21T08:57:06.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13586",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The quote() method returns a string surrounded by quotes, and with internal characters escaped as needed.  This is how the quote() method in Zend_Db is designed.  There are some cases where using quote() is unnecessary, and you are correct that using it will cause problems.\n\nThere is no need to use the quote() method if you are inserting strings as parameters.\n\nWrong:\n{code}\n$db->insert('table', array('col1' => $db->quote(\"O'Reilly\"))); \n{code}\n\nRight:\n{code}\n$db->insert('table', array('col1' => \"O'Reilly\")); \n{code}\n\nBut there is a need to use the quote() method if you are interpolating strings directly into SQL expressions:\n\nWrong:\n{code}\n$value = \"O'Reilly\";\n$sql = 'INSERT INTO table (col1) VALUES ( $value )';\n$db->query($sql);\n{code}\n\nRight:\n{code}\n$value = $db->quote(\"O'Reilly\");\n$sql = 'INSERT INTO table (col1) VALUES ( $value )';\n$db->query($sql);\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-21T12:13:54.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-21T12:13:54.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13587",
                    "author": {
